<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>On line 170 of Zend_Translate_Plural the country code 'sl' is given for the plural format on line 171:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
            case 'sl':
                return ($number % 100 == 1) ? 0 : (($number % 100 == 2) ? 1 : ((($number % 100 == 3) || ($number % 100 == 4)) ? 2 : 3));
</code></pre>

<p>The country code 'sl' stands for Sierra Leone, while, according to the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/s/hello/manual/gettext/Plural-forms.html">GNU gettext documentation</a>, the given plural format should reflect Slavic languages. The official language of Sierra Leone is English, so 'sl' should probably be 'si', which is the correct country code for Slovenia (<a href="http://www.iso.org/iso/country_codes/iso_3166_code_lists/country_names_and_code_elements.htm">ISO 3166 country codes</a>).</p>

