        <div class="body">
            <p>You missunderstood the code. Zend_Translate does translations... this means it works on languages not on country codes.
According to unicode "sl" stands for the language "slovenish", whereas "SL" (note the uppercase notation) stands as you wrote for Sierra Leone.
As plural forms are always used on languages (plurals are not country related but only related to a language) the code is designed as wished.</p>

